doc.previous: European integration is the process of political legal economic and in some cases social and cultural integration of states wholly or partially in Europe In the present day European integration has primarily come about through the Council of Europe and European Union in Western and Central Europe and Commonwealth of Independent States in Central and Eastern Europe and most of former Soviet countries
